cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision tasks, specifically image classification on the ImageNet dataset. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of a larger model as a student, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the use of pseudo-labels and data augmentation techniques are common in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL) tasks. Finally, the paper mentions the use of stochastic depth, which is a technique commonly used in neural networks (cs.NE).
